enges the main themes of an entire generation of scholarship about the social conflicts of China's Cultural Revolution, shedding light on the most tragic and poorly understood period of recent Chinese history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPolitical violencezChinazBeijingxHistoryy20th century. 0aProtest movementszChinazBeijingxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial conflictzChinazBeijingxHistoryy20th century. 0aStudent movementszChinazBeijingxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674054783?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674054783423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674054783/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK